<subSubSection id="C3325FC70846FFE0998BFDAE33FEFBD6" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8B970C4C0846FFE0998BFDAE362DFD0F" blockId="6.[166,1225,367,1034]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">
Biology. The specimens were captured in litter of dry open places (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB971BD0846FFE09D47FDAE3696FD2C" author="Esyunin, S. L." box="[1047,1221,623,649]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" pagination="136 - 139" refId="ref3144" refString="Esyunin, S. L. 1992. Remarks on the Ural spider (Arachnida, Aranei) fauna. 2. A new genus and a new species of the family Linyphiidae. Zoologicheskij Zhurnal, 71 (12), 136 - 139." type="journal article" year="1992">Esyunin, 1992</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB971BD0846FFE099F6FD5133E4FD0F" author="Ponomarev, A. V. &amp; Prokopenko, E. V. &amp; Shmatko, V. Yu." box="[166,439,655,682]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" pagination="103 - 117" refId="ref3498" refString="Ponomarev, A. V., Prokopenko, E. V., Shmatko, V. Yu. 2017. New and interesting records of spiders (Arachnida: Aranei) from the southeastern part of the Russian Plain. Proceedings of the Russian Entomological Society, 88 (1), 103 - 117." type="journal article" year="2017">Ponomarev et al., 2017</bibRefCitation>
), on the grass in patch forest with birch (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB971BD0846FFE09AC4FD4E3622FD0F" author="Azheganova, N. S." box="[916,1137,655,682]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" pagination="137 - 156" refId="ref3105" refString="Azheganova, N. S. 1951. To the spider fauna of the Troitsky Forest-Steppe Reserve. Izvestija Yestestvenno- - Nauchnogo Instituta pri Molotovskom Gosudarstvennom Universitete, 13 (2 - 3), 137 - 156." type="journal article" year="1951">Azheganova, 1951</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B970C4C0846FFE0998BFD6E31FFFCAC" blockId="6.[166,1225,367,1034]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">
C o m m e n t s: Data on 
<taxonomicName id="4C2877CF0846FFE098B4FD713162FD6C" authority="Esyunin, 1992" authorityName="Esyunin" authorityYear="1992" box="[484,817,687,713]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Uralophantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="troitskensis">
<emphasis id="B95CD05E0846FFE098B4FD7130D4FD6C" box="[484,647,687,713]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">U. troitskensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB971BD0846FFE09BDDFD6E3162FD6C" author="Esyunin, S. L." box="[653,817,687,713]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" pagination="136 - 139" refId="ref3144" refString="Esyunin, S. L. 1992. Remarks on the Ural spider (Arachnida, Aranei) fauna. 2. A new genus and a new species of the family Linyphiidae. Zoologicheskij Zhurnal, 71 (12), 136 - 139." type="journal article" year="1992">
Esyunin, 
<quantity id="4CD0A1A90846FFE09BA9FD6E3162FD6C" box="[761,817,687,713]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.05968" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" unit="in" value="1992.0">1992</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in both 
<collectingRegion id="49ECC2AE0846FFE09AC1FD6E364EFD6C" box="[913,1053,687,713]" country="Russia" name="Chelyabinsk" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Cheliabinsk</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="49ECC2AE0846FFE09D04FD6E369BFD6C" box="[1108,1224,687,713]" country="Russia" name="Orenburg" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Orenburg</collectingRegion>
Regions were confirmed by Sergey Esyunin. For the rest points in 
<collectingCountry id="F33F4CDC0846FFE09AF3FD0E31A1FD4C" box="[931,1010,719,745]" name="Russia" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Russia</collectingCountry>
, the correctness of identification of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2877CF0846FFE09839FD3130EAFCAC" authority="Esyunin, 1992" authorityName="Esyunin" authorityYear="1992" box="[361,697,751,777]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Uralophantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="troitskensis">
<emphasis id="B95CD05E0846FFE09839FD31305FFCAC" box="[361,524,751,777]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">U. troitskensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB971BD0846FFE09B43FD2E30EAFCAC" author="Esyunin, S. L." box="[531,697,751,777]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" pagination="136 - 139" refId="ref3144" refString="Esyunin, S. L. 1992. Remarks on the Ural spider (Arachnida, Aranei) fauna. 2. A new genus and a new species of the family Linyphiidae. Zoologicheskij Zhurnal, 71 (12), 136 - 139." type="journal article" year="1992">Esyunin, 1992</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
need corroboration.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B970C4C0846FFE0998BFCCE3354FBAF" blockId="6.[166,1225,367,1034]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">
Discussion. Drawings of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2877CF0846FFE09B69FCD130B6FC8C" authorityName="Esyunin" authorityYear="1992" box="[569,741,783,809]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Uralophantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="troitskensis">
<emphasis id="B95CD05E0846FFE09B69FCD130B6FC8C" box="[569,741,783,809]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">U. troitskensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
male palp, although being somewhat schematic, nonetheless are accurate enough for comparison of two 
<taxonomicName id="4C2877CF0846FFE09A9AFCEE369AFCEC" box="[970,1225,815,841]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Uralophantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B95CD05E0846FFE09A9AFCEE3634FCEC" box="[970,1127,815,841]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Uralophantes</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
Judging from the figures certain palp parts of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2877CF0846FFE09B94FC91313BFCCC" authorityName="Esyunin" authorityYear="1992" box="[708,872,847,873]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Uralophantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="troitskensis">
<emphasis id="B95CD05E0846FFE09B94FC91313BFCCC" box="[708,872,847,873]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">U. troitskensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ in structure from those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2877CF0846FFE0999AFCB13301FC2C" authority="Gnelitsa, 2022" authorityName="Gnelitsa" authorityYear="2022" box="[202,338,880,905]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Uralophantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ponticus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B95CD05E0846FFE0999AFCB13301FC2C" box="[202,338,880,905]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">U. ponticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26F6D250846FFE0980EFCB133F2FC2F" box="[350,417,880,906]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
or entirely absent of all examined specimens of the new species. Beside that the palps of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2877CF0846FFE09891FC513016FC0C" authority="Gnelitsa, 2022" authorityName="Gnelitsa" authorityYear="2022" box="[449,581,912,937]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Uralophantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ponticus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B95CD05E0846FFE09891FC513016FC0C" box="[449,581,912,937]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">U. ponticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26F6D250846FFE09B1DFC5130DFFC0F" box="[589,652,912,938]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
from remote places (
<collectingRegion id="49ECC2AE0846FFE09AD8FC4E319CFC0C" box="[904,975,911,937]" country="Ukraine" name="Sumy" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Sumy</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49ECC2AE0846FFE09A8CFC4E3610FC0C" box="[988,1091,911,937]" country="Ukraine" name="Kherson" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Kherson</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion id="49ECC2AE0846FFE09DD2FC51369BFC0F" box="[1154,1224,912,938]" country="Russia" name="Penza" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Penza</collectingRegion>
Regions) are quite conservative in their structure. Thus I consider 
<taxonomicName id="4C2877CF0846FFE09AF2FC713677FC6C" authority="Gnelitsa, 2022" authorityName="Gnelitsa" authorityYear="2022" box="[930,1060,944,969]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Uralophantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ponticus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B95CD05E0846FFE09AF2FC713677FC6C" box="[930,1060,944,969]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">U. ponticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26F6D250846FFE09D7AFC713635FC6F" box="[1066,1126,944,970]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
